        {
            "title": "Fanatics Launches Prediction Market Platform",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Josh Beckerman </p><br/><p>\n  Fanatics said it launched prediction market platform Fanatics Markets, providing \"a safe and fun way to pick a side and potentially profit on the outcomes that matter most, whether that's a sporting event, the Oscars, an election, or a cultural moment.\" </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  Fanatics Markets formed a partnership with Crypto.com | Derivatives North America. </p><p>\n\n  Prediction markets have gained popularity, media coverage and investments amid a changing regulatory environment. PredictIt offers a range of political markets ranging from 2028 presidential nominees to \"First Cabinet member to leave in 2025?\" Polymarket's trending items include a wide range of politics and sports options, as well as \"Will Polymarket US go live in 2025?\" </p><p>\n\n  Fanatics Markets will launch in 24 states including California, Texas, Florida and Washington. </p><p>\n\n  FanDuel and CME Group said last month that they would launch a prediction markets platform in December. </p><p>\n\n  Kalshi said Tuesday that it raised $1 billion at an $11 billion valuation. New York Stock Exchange owner Intercontinental Exchange said in October that it would invest up to $2 billion in Polymarket, reflecting a valuation of about $8 billion pre-investment. </p><br/><p>\n  Write to Josh Beckerman at josh.beckerman@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  12-03-25 1608ET</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/fanatics-launches-prediction-market-platform-ce7d51ded18ff327",
            "pub_date": "2025-12-04 05:10:41",
            "source": "marketscreener",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        },
